452inline bool isInvalidData(double value) {
453 return qIsNaN(value) || qIsInf(value);
454}
455
461inline bool isInvalidData(double value1, double value2) {
462 return isInvalidData(value1) || isInvalidData(value2);
463}
464
471inline void setMarginValue(QMargins &margins, QCP::MarginSide side, int value) {
472 switch (side) {
473 case QCP::msLeft:
474 margins.setLeft(value);
475 break;
476 case QCP::msRight:
477 margins.setRight(value);
478 break;
479 case QCP::msTop:
480 margins.setTop(value);
481 break;
482 case QCP::msBottom:
483 margins.setBottom(value);
484 break;
485 case QCP::msAll:
486 margins = QMargins(value, value, value, value);
487 break;
488 default:
489 break;
490 }
491}
492
500inline int getMarginValue(const QMargins &margins, QCP::MarginSide side) {
501 switch (side) {
502 case QCP::msLeft:
503 return margins.left();
504 case QCP::msRight:
505 return margins.right();
506 case QCP::msTop:
507 return margins.top();
508 case QCP::msBottom:
509 return margins.bottom();
510 default:
511 break;
512 }
513 return 0;
514}

567class QCP_LIB_DECL QCPVector2D {
568 public:
569 QCPVector2D();
570 QCPVector2D(double x, double y);
571 QCPVector2D(const QPoint &point);
572 QCPVector2D(const QPointF &point);
573
574 // getters:
575 double x() const { return mX; }
576 double y() const { return mY; }
577 double &rx() { return mX; }
578 double &ry() { return mY; }
579
580 // setters:
581 void setX(double x) { mX = x; }
582 void setY(double y) { mY = y; }
583
584 // non-virtual methods:
585 double length() const { return qSqrt(mX * mX + mY * mY); }
586 double lengthSquared() const { return mX * mX + mY * mY; }
587 double angle() const { return qAtan2(mY, mX); }
588 QPoint toPoint() const { return QPoint(int(mX), int(mY)); }
589 QPointF toPointF() const { return QPointF(mX, mY); }
590
591 bool isNull() const { return qIsNull(mX) && qIsNull(mY); }
592 void normalize();
593 QCPVector2D normalized() const;
594 QCPVector2D perpendicular() const { return QCPVector2D(-mY, mX); }
595 double dot(const QCPVector2D &vec) const { return mX * vec.mX + mY * vec.mY; }
596 double distanceSquaredToLine(const QCPVector2D &start,
597 const QCPVector2D &end) const;
598 double distanceSquaredToLine(const QLineF &line) const;
599 double distanceToStraightLine(const QCPVector2D &base,
600 const QCPVector2D &direction) const;
601
602 QCPVector2D &operator*=(double factor);
603 QCPVector2D &operator/=(double divisor);
604 QCPVector2D &operator+=(const QCPVector2D &vector);
605 QCPVector2D &operator-=(const QCPVector2D &vector);
606
607 private:
608 // property members:
609 double mX, mY;
610
611 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator*(double factor,
612 const QCPVector2D &vec);
613 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator*(const QCPVector2D &vec,
614 double factor);
615 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator/(const QCPVector2D &vec,
616 double divisor);
617 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator+(const QCPVector2D &vec1,
618 const QCPVector2D &vec2);
619 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec1,
620 const QCPVector2D &vec2);
621 friend inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec);
622};
623Q_DECLARE_TYPEINFO(QCPVector2D, Q_MOVABLE_TYPE);
624
625inline const QCPVector2D operator*(double factor, const QCPVector2D &vec) {
626 return QCPVector2D(vec.mX * factor, vec.mY * factor);
627}
628inline const QCPVector2D operator*(const QCPVector2D &vec, double factor) {
629 return QCPVector2D(vec.mX * factor, vec.mY * factor);
630}
631inline const QCPVector2D operator/(const QCPVector2D &vec, double divisor) {
632 return QCPVector2D(vec.mX / divisor, vec.mY / divisor);
633}
634inline const QCPVector2D operator+(const QCPVector2D &vec1,
635 const QCPVector2D &vec2) {
636 return QCPVector2D(vec1.mX + vec2.mX, vec1.mY + vec2.mY);
637}
638inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec1,
639 const QCPVector2D &vec2) {
640 return QCPVector2D(vec1.mX - vec2.mX, vec1.mY - vec2.mY);
641}
642inline const QCPVector2D operator-(const QCPVector2D &vec) {
643 return QCPVector2D(-vec.mX, -vec.mY);
644}
645
650inline QDebug operator<<(QDebug d, const QCPVector2D &vec) {
651 d.nospace() << "QCPVector2D(" << vec.x() << ", " << vec.y() << ")";
652 return d.space();
653}

990class QCP_LIB_DECL QCPRange {
991 public:
992 double lower, upper;
993
994 QCPRange();
995 QCPRange(double lower, double upper);
996
997 bool operator==(const QCPRange &other) const {
998 return lower == other.lower && upper == other.upper;
999 }
1000 bool operator!=(const QCPRange &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
1001
1002 QCPRange &operator+=(const double &value) {
1003 lower += value;
1004 upper += value;
1005 return *this;
1006 }
1007 QCPRange &operator-=(const double &value) {
1008 lower -= value;
1009 upper -= value;
1010 return *this;
1011 }
1012 QCPRange &operator*=(const double &value) {
1013 lower *= value;
1014 upper *= value;
1015 return *this;
1016 }
1017 QCPRange &operator/=(const double &value) {
1018 lower /= value;
1019 upper /= value;
1020 return *this;
1021 }
1022 friend inline const QCPRange operator+(const QCPRange &, double);
1023 friend inline const QCPRange operator+(double, const QCPRange &);
1024 friend inline const QCPRange operator-(const QCPRange &range, double value);
1025 friend inline const QCPRange operator*(const QCPRange &range, double value);
1026 friend inline const QCPRange operator*(double value, const QCPRange &range);
1027 friend inline const QCPRange operator/(const QCPRange &range, double value);
1028
1029 double size() const { return upper - lower; }
1030 double center() const { return (upper + lower) * 0.5; }
1031 void normalize() {
1032 if (lower > upper) qSwap(lower, upper);
1033 }
1034 void expand(const QCPRange &otherRange);
1035 void expand(double includeCoord);
1036 QCPRange expanded(const QCPRange &otherRange) const;
1037 QCPRange expanded(double includeCoord) const;
1038 QCPRange bounded(double lowerBound, double upperBound) const;
1039 QCPRange sanitizedForLogScale() const;
1040 QCPRange sanitizedForLinScale() const;
1041 bool contains(double value) const { return value >= lower && value <= upper; }
1042
1043 static bool validRange(double lower, double upper);
1044 static bool validRange(const QCPRange &range);
1045 static const double minRange;
1046 static const double maxRange;
1047};
1048Q_DECLARE_TYPEINFO(QCPRange, Q_MOVABLE_TYPE);

2983template <class DataType>
2984inline bool qcpLessThanSortKey(const DataType &a, const DataType &b) {
2985 return a.sortKey() < b.sortKey();
2986}

3248template <class DataType>
3249void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::set(const QVector<DataType> &data,
3250 bool alreadySorted) {
3251 mData = data;
3252 mPreallocSize = 0;
3253 mPreallocIteration = 0;
3254 if (!alreadySorted) sort();
3255}
3256
3263template <class DataType>
3264void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::add(const QCPDataContainer<DataType> &data) {
3265 if (data.isEmpty()) return;
3266
3267 const int n = data.size();
3268 const int oldSize = size();
3269
3270 if (oldSize > 0 &&
3271 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3272 *constBegin(),
3273 *(data.constEnd() - 1))) // prepend if new data keys are all smaller
3274 // than or equal to existing ones
3275 {
3276 if (mPreallocSize < n) preallocateGrow(n);
3277 mPreallocSize -= n;
3278 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), begin());
3279 } else // don't need to prepend, so append and merge if necessary
3280 {
3281 mData.resize(mData.size() + n);
3282 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), end() - n);
3283 if (oldSize > 0 &&
3284 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3285 *(constEnd() - n - 1),
3286 *(constEnd() - n))) // if appended range keys aren't all greater
3287 // than existing ones, merge the two partitions
3288 std::inplace_merge(begin(), end() - n, end(),
3289 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3290 }
3291}
3292
3302template <class DataType>
3303void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::add(const QVector<DataType> &data,
3304 bool alreadySorted) {
3305 if (data.isEmpty()) return;
3306 if (isEmpty()) {
3307 set(data, alreadySorted);
3308 return;
3309 }
3310
3311 const int n = data.size();
3312 const int oldSize = size();
3313
3314 if (alreadySorted && oldSize > 0 &&
3315 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3316 *constBegin(), *(data.constEnd() -
3317 1))) // prepend if new data is sorted and keys are
3318 // all smaller than or equal to existing ones
3319 {
3320 if (mPreallocSize < n) preallocateGrow(n);
3321 mPreallocSize -= n;
3322 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), begin());
3323 } else // don't need to prepend, so append and then sort and merge if
3324 // necessary
3325 {
3326 mData.resize(mData.size() + n);
3327 std::copy(data.constBegin(), data.constEnd(), end() - n);
3328 if (!alreadySorted) // sort appended subrange if it wasn't already sorted
3329 std::sort(end() - n, end(), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3330 if (oldSize > 0 &&
3331 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3332 *(constEnd() - n - 1),
3333 *(constEnd() - n))) // if appended range keys aren't all greater
3334 // than existing ones, merge the two partitions
3335 std::inplace_merge(begin(), end() - n, end(),
3336 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3337 }
3338}
3339
3346template <class DataType>
3347void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::add(const DataType &data) {
3348 if (isEmpty() ||
3349 !qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3350 data, *(constEnd() - 1))) // quickly handle appends if new data key
3351 // is greater or equal to existing ones
3352 {
3353 mData.append(data);
3354 } else if (qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>(
3355 data, *constBegin())) // quickly handle prepends using
3356 // preallocated space
3357 {
3358 if (mPreallocSize < 1) preallocateGrow(1);
3359 --mPreallocSize;
3360 *begin() = data;
3361 } else // handle inserts, maintaining sorted keys
3362 {
3363 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator insertionPoint =
3364 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), data, qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3365 mData.insert(insertionPoint, data);
3366 }
3367}
3368
3374template <class DataType>
3375void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::removeBefore(double sortKey) {
3376 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator it = begin();
3377 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator itEnd =
3378 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey),
3379 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3380 mPreallocSize +=
3381 int(itEnd -
3382 it); // don't actually delete, just add it to the preallocated block
3383 // (if it gets too large, squeeze will take care of it)
3384 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3385}
3386
3392template <class DataType>
3393void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::removeAfter(double sortKey) {
3394 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator it =
3395 std::upper_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey),
3396 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3397 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator itEnd = end();
3398 mData.erase(it, itEnd); // typically adds it to the postallocated block
3399 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3400}
3401
3410template <class DataType>
3411void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::remove(double sortKeyFrom, double sortKeyTo) {
3412 if (sortKeyFrom >= sortKeyTo || isEmpty()) return;
3413
3414 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator it =
3415 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKeyFrom),
3416 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3417 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::iterator itEnd =
3418 std::upper_bound(it, end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKeyTo),
3419 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3420 mData.erase(it, itEnd);
3421 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3422}
3423
3433template <class DataType>
3434void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::remove(double sortKey) {
3435 QCPDataContainer::iterator it =
3436 std::lower_bound(begin(), end(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey),
3437 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3438 if (it != end() && it->sortKey() == sortKey) {
3439 if (it == begin())
3440 ++mPreallocSize; // don't actually delete, just add it to the
3441 // preallocated block (if it gets too large, squeeze
3442 // will take care of it)
3443 else
3444 mData.erase(it);
3445 }
3446 if (mAutoSqueeze) performAutoSqueeze();
3447}
3448
3454template <class DataType>
3455void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::clear() {
3456 mData.clear();
3457 mPreallocIteration = 0;
3458 mPreallocSize = 0;
3459}
3460
3473template <class DataType>
3474void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::sort() {
3475 std::sort(begin(), end(), qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3476}
3477
3489template <class DataType>
3490void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::squeeze(bool preAllocation,
3491 bool postAllocation) {
3492 if (preAllocation) {
3493 if (mPreallocSize > 0) {
3494 std::copy(begin(), end(), mData.begin());
3495 mData.resize(size());
3496 mPreallocSize = 0;
3497 }
3498 mPreallocIteration = 0;
3499 }
3500 if (postAllocation) mData.squeeze();
3501}
3502
3519template <class DataType>
3520typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator
3521QCPDataContainer<DataType>::findBegin(double sortKey,
3522 bool expandedRange) const {
3523 if (isEmpty()) return constEnd();
3524
3525 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it =
3526 std::lower_bound(constBegin(), constEnd(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey),
3527 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3528 if (expandedRange &&
3529 it != constBegin()) // also covers it == constEnd case, and we know
3530 // --constEnd is valid because mData isn't empty
3531 --it;
3532 return it;
3533}
3534
3552template <class DataType>
3553typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator
3554QCPDataContainer<DataType>::findEnd(double sortKey, bool expandedRange) const {
3555 if (isEmpty()) return constEnd();
3556
3557 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it =
3558 std::upper_bound(constBegin(), constEnd(), DataType::fromSortKey(sortKey),
3559 qcpLessThanSortKey<DataType>);
3560 if (expandedRange && it != constEnd()) ++it;
3561 return it;
3562}
3563
3580template <class DataType>
3581QCPRange QCPDataContainer<DataType>::keyRange(bool &foundRange,
3582 QCP::SignDomain signDomain) {
3583 if (isEmpty()) {
3584 foundRange = false;
3585 return QCPRange();
3586 }
3587 QCPRange range;
3588 bool haveLower = false;
3589 bool haveUpper = false;
3590 double current;
3591
3592 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = constBegin();
3593 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator itEnd = constEnd();
3594 if (signDomain == QCP::sdBoth) // range may be anywhere
3595 {
3596 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey()) // if DataType is sorted by main key
3597 // (e.g. QCPGraph, but not QCPCurve), use
3598 // faster algorithm by finding just first
3599 // and last key with non-NaN value
3600 {
3601 while (it != itEnd) // find first non-nan going up from left
3602 {
3603 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3604 range.lower = it->mainKey();
3605 haveLower = true;
3606 break;
3607 }
3608 ++it;
3609 }
3610 it = itEnd;
3611 while (it != constBegin()) // find first non-nan going down from right
3612 {
3613 --it;
3614 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3615 range.upper = it->mainKey();
3616 haveUpper = true;
3617 break;
3618 }
3619 }
3620 } else // DataType is not sorted by main key, go through all data points
3621 // and accordingly expand range
3622 {
3623 while (it != itEnd) {
3624 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3625 current = it->mainKey();
3626 if (current < range.lower || !haveLower) {
3627 range.lower = current;
3628 haveLower = true;
3629 }
3630 if (current > range.upper || !haveUpper) {
3631 range.upper = current;
3632 haveUpper = true;
3633 }
3634 }
3635 ++it;
3636 }
3637 }
3638 } else if (signDomain ==
3639 QCP::sdNegative) // range may only be in the negative sign domain
3640 {
3641 while (it != itEnd) {
3642 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3643 current = it->mainKey();
3644 if ((current < range.lower || !haveLower) && current < 0) {
3645 range.lower = current;
3646 haveLower = true;
3647 }
3648 if ((current > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current < 0) {
3649 range.upper = current;
3650 haveUpper = true;
3651 }
3652 }
3653 ++it;
3654 }
3655 } else if (signDomain ==
3656 QCP::sdPositive) // range may only be in the positive sign domain
3657 {
3658 while (it != itEnd) {
3659 if (!qIsNaN(it->mainValue())) {
3660 current = it->mainKey();
3661 if ((current < range.lower || !haveLower) && current > 0) {
3662 range.lower = current;
3663 haveLower = true;
3664 }
3665 if ((current > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current > 0) {
3666 range.upper = current;
3667 haveUpper = true;
3668 }
3669 }
3670 ++it;
3671 }
3672 }
3673
3674 foundRange = haveLower && haveUpper;
3675 return range;
3676}
3677
3698template <class DataType>
3699QCPRange QCPDataContainer<DataType>::valueRange(bool &foundRange,
3700 QCP::SignDomain signDomain,
3701 const QCPRange &inKeyRange) {
3702 if (isEmpty()) {
3703 foundRange = false;
3704 return QCPRange();
3705 }
3706 QCPRange range;
3707 const bool restrictKeyRange = inKeyRange != QCPRange();
3708 bool haveLower = false;
3709 bool haveUpper = false;
3710 QCPRange current;
3711 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator itBegin = constBegin();
3712 QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator itEnd = constEnd();
3713 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey() && restrictKeyRange) {
3714 itBegin = findBegin(inKeyRange.lower, false);
3715 itEnd = findEnd(inKeyRange.upper, false);
3716 }
3717 if (signDomain == QCP::sdBoth) // range may be anywhere
3718 {
3719 for (QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = itBegin; it != itEnd;
3720 ++it) {
3721 if (restrictKeyRange && (it->mainKey() < inKeyRange.lower ||
3722 it->mainKey() > inKeyRange.upper))
3723 continue;
3724 current = it->valueRange();
3725 if ((current.lower < range.lower || !haveLower) &&
3726 !qIsNaN(current.lower) && std::isfinite(current.lower)) {
3727 range.lower = current.lower;
3728 haveLower = true;
3729 }
3730 if ((current.upper > range.upper || !haveUpper) &&
3731 !qIsNaN(current.upper) && std::isfinite(current.upper)) {
3732 range.upper = current.upper;
3733 haveUpper = true;
3734 }
3735 }
3736 } else if (signDomain ==
3737 QCP::sdNegative) // range may only be in the negative sign domain
3738 {
3739 for (QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = itBegin; it != itEnd;
3740 ++it) {
3741 if (restrictKeyRange && (it->mainKey() < inKeyRange.lower ||
3742 it->mainKey() > inKeyRange.upper))
3743 continue;
3744 current = it->valueRange();
3745 if ((current.lower < range.lower || !haveLower) && current.lower < 0 &&
3746 !qIsNaN(current.lower) && std::isfinite(current.lower)) {
3747 range.lower = current.lower;
3748 haveLower = true;
3749 }
3750 if ((current.upper > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current.upper < 0 &&
3751 !qIsNaN(current.upper) && std::isfinite(current.upper)) {
3752 range.upper = current.upper;
3753 haveUpper = true;
3754 }
3755 }
3756 } else if (signDomain ==
3757 QCP::sdPositive) // range may only be in the positive sign domain
3758 {
3759 for (QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = itBegin; it != itEnd;
3760 ++it) {
3761 if (restrictKeyRange && (it->mainKey() < inKeyRange.lower ||
3762 it->mainKey() > inKeyRange.upper))
3763 continue;
3764 current = it->valueRange();
3765 if ((current.lower < range.lower || !haveLower) && current.lower > 0 &&
3766 !qIsNaN(current.lower) && std::isfinite(current.lower)) {
3767 range.lower = current.lower;
3768 haveLower = true;
3769 }
3770 if ((current.upper > range.upper || !haveUpper) && current.upper > 0 &&
3771 !qIsNaN(current.upper) && std::isfinite(current.upper)) {
3772 range.upper = current.upper;
3773 haveUpper = true;
3774 }
3775 }
3776 }
3777
3778 foundRange = haveLower && haveUpper;
3779 return range;
3780}

3791template <class DataType>
3792void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::limitIteratorsToDataRange(
3793 const_iterator &begin, const_iterator &end,
3794 const QCPDataRange &dataRange) const {
3795 QCPDataRange iteratorRange(int(begin - constBegin()),
3796 int(end - constBegin()));
3797 iteratorRange = iteratorRange.bounded(dataRange.bounded(this->dataRange()));
3798 begin = constBegin() + iteratorRange.begin();
3799 end = constBegin() + iteratorRange.end();
3800}
3801
3812template <class DataType>
3813void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::preallocateGrow(int minimumPreallocSize) {
3814 if (minimumPreallocSize <= mPreallocSize) return;
3815
3816 int newPreallocSize = minimumPreallocSize;
3817 newPreallocSize += (1u << qBound(4, mPreallocIteration + 4, 15)) -
3818 12; // do 4 up to 32768-12 preallocation, doubling in each
3819 // intermediate iteration
3820 ++mPreallocIteration;
3821
3822 int sizeDifference = newPreallocSize - mPreallocSize;
3823 mData.resize(mData.size() + sizeDifference);
3824 std::copy_backward(mData.begin() + mPreallocSize,
3825 mData.end() - sizeDifference, mData.end());
3826 mPreallocSize = newPreallocSize;
3827}
3828
3845template <class DataType>
3846void QCPDataContainer<DataType>::performAutoSqueeze() {
3847 const int totalAlloc = mData.capacity();
3848 const int postAllocSize = totalAlloc - mData.size();
3849 const int usedSize = size();
3850 bool shrinkPostAllocation = false;
3851 bool shrinkPreAllocation = false;
3852 if (totalAlloc > 650000) // if allocation is larger, shrink earlier with
3853 // respect to total used size
3854 {
3855 shrinkPostAllocation =
3856 postAllocSize >
3857 usedSize * 1.5; // QVector grow strategy is 2^n for static data. Watch
3858 // out not to oscillate!
3859 shrinkPreAllocation = mPreallocSize * 10 > usedSize;
3860 } else if (totalAlloc >
3861 1000) // below 10 MiB raw data be generous with preallocated
3862 // memory, below 1k points don't even bother
3863 {
3864 shrinkPostAllocation = postAllocSize > usedSize * 5;
3865 shrinkPreAllocation =
3866 mPreallocSize > usedSize * 1.5; // preallocation can grow into
3867 // postallocation, so can be smaller
3868 }
3869
3870 if (shrinkPreAllocation || shrinkPostAllocation)
3871 squeeze(shrinkPreAllocation, shrinkPostAllocation);
3872}

4599// implementation of template functions:
4600
4620template <class PlottableType>
4621PlottableType *QCustomPlot::plottableAt(const QPointF &pos, bool onlySelectable,
4622 int *dataIndex) const {
4623 PlottableType *resultPlottable = 0;
4624 QVariant resultDetails;
4625 double resultDistance =
4626 mSelectionTolerance; // only regard clicks with distances smaller than
4627 // mSelectionTolerance as selections, so initialize
4628 // with that value
4629
4630 foreach (QCPAbstractPlottable *plottable, mPlottables) {
4631 PlottableType *currentPlottable = qobject_cast<PlottableType *>(plottable);
4632 if (!currentPlottable ||
4633 (onlySelectable &&
4634 !currentPlottable
4635 ->selectable())) // we could have also passed onlySelectable to
4636 // the selectTest function, but checking here is
4637 // faster, because we have access to
4638 // QCPAbstractPlottable::selectable
4639 continue;
4640 if (currentPlottable->clipRect().contains(
4641 pos.toPoint())) // only consider clicks where the plottable is
4642 // actually visible
4643 {
4644 QVariant details;
4645 double currentDistance = currentPlottable->selectTest(
4646 pos, false, dataIndex ? &details : nullptr);
4647 if (currentDistance >= 0 && currentDistance < resultDistance) {
4648 resultPlottable = currentPlottable;
4649 resultDetails = details;
4650 resultDistance = currentDistance;
4651 }
4652 }
4653 }
4654
4655 if (resultPlottable && dataIndex) {
4656 QCPDataSelection sel = resultDetails.value<QCPDataSelection>();
4657 if (!sel.isEmpty()) *dataIndex = sel.dataRange(0).begin();
4658 }
4659 return resultPlottable;
4660}
4661
4677template <class ItemType>
4678ItemType *QCustomPlot::itemAt(const QPointF &pos, bool onlySelectable) const {
4679 ItemType *resultItem = 0;
4680 double resultDistance =
4681 mSelectionTolerance; // only regard clicks with distances smaller than
4682 // mSelectionTolerance as selections, so initialize
4683 // with that value
4684
4685 foreach (QCPAbstractItem *item, mItems) {
4686 ItemType *currentItem = qobject_cast<ItemType *>(item);
4687 if (!currentItem ||
4688 (onlySelectable &&
4689 !currentItem
4690 ->selectable())) // we could have also passed onlySelectable to
4691 // the selectTest function, but checking here is
4692 // faster, because we have access to
4693 // QCPAbstractItem::selectable
4694 continue;
4695 if (!currentItem->clipToAxisRect() ||
4696 currentItem->clipRect().contains(
4697 pos.toPoint())) // only consider clicks inside axis cliprect of the
4698 // item if actually clipped to it
4699 {
4700 double currentDistance = currentItem->selectTest(pos, false);
4701 if (currentDistance >= 0 && currentDistance < resultDistance) {
4702 resultItem = currentItem;
4703 resultDistance = currentDistance;
4704 }
4705 }
4706 }
4707
4708 return resultItem;
4709}

5081
5090template <class DataType>
5091QCPDataSelection QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::selectTestRect(
5092 const QRectF &rect, bool onlySelectable) const {
5093 QCPDataSelection result;
5094 if ((onlySelectable && mSelectable == QCP::stNone) ||
5095 mDataContainer->isEmpty())
5096 return result;
5097 if (!mKeyAxis || !mValueAxis) return result;
5098
5099 // convert rect given in pixels to ranges given in plot coordinates:
5100 double key1, value1, key2, value2;
5101 pixelsToCoords(rect.topLeft(), key1, value1);
5102 pixelsToCoords(rect.bottomRight(), key2, value2);
5103 QCPRange keyRange(key1, key2); // QCPRange normalizes internally so we don't
5104 // have to care about whether key1 < key2
5105 QCPRange valueRange(value1, value2);
5106 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator begin =
5107 mDataContainer->constBegin();
5108 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator end =
5109 mDataContainer->constEnd();
5110 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey()) // we can assume that data is sorted by
5111 // main key, so can reduce the searched key
5112 // interval:
5113 {
5114 begin = mDataContainer->findBegin(keyRange.lower, false);
5115 end = mDataContainer->findEnd(keyRange.upper, false);
5116 }
5117 if (begin == end) return result;
5118
5119 int currentSegmentBegin =
5120 -1; // -1 means we're currently not in a segment that's contained in rect
5121 for (typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = begin;
5122 it != end; ++it) {
5123 if (currentSegmentBegin == -1) {
5124 if (valueRange.contains(it->mainValue()) &&
5125 keyRange.contains(it->mainKey())) // start segment
5126 currentSegmentBegin = int(it - mDataContainer->constBegin());
5127 } else if (!valueRange.contains(it->mainValue()) ||
5128 !keyRange.contains(it->mainKey())) // segment just ended
5129 {
5130 result.addDataRange(QCPDataRange(currentSegmentBegin,
5131 int(it - mDataContainer->constBegin())),
5132 false);
5133 currentSegmentBegin = -1;
5134 }
5135 }
5136 // process potential last segment:
5137 if (currentSegmentBegin != -1)
5138 result.addDataRange(QCPDataRange(currentSegmentBegin,
5139 int(end - mDataContainer->constBegin())),
5140 false);
5141
5142 result.simplify();
5143 return result;
5144}
5145
5149template <class DataType>
5150int QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::findBegin(double sortKey,
5151 bool expandedRange) const {
5152 return int(mDataContainer->findBegin(sortKey, expandedRange) -
5153 mDataContainer->constBegin());
5154}
5155
5159template <class DataType>
5160int QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::findEnd(double sortKey,
5161 bool expandedRange) const {
5162 return int(mDataContainer->findEnd(sortKey, expandedRange) -
5163 mDataContainer->constBegin());
5164}
5165
5177template <class DataType>
5178double QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::selectTest(const QPointF &pos,
5179 bool onlySelectable,
5180 QVariant *details) const {
5181 if ((onlySelectable && mSelectable == QCP::stNone) ||
5182 mDataContainer->isEmpty())
5183 return -1;
5184 if (!mKeyAxis || !mValueAxis) return -1;
5185
5186 QCPDataSelection selectionResult;
5187 double minDistSqr = (std::numeric_limits<double>::max)();
5188 int minDistIndex = mDataContainer->size();
5189
5190 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator begin =
5191 mDataContainer->constBegin();
5192 typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator end =
5193 mDataContainer->constEnd();
5194 if (DataType::sortKeyIsMainKey()) // we can assume that data is sorted by
5195 // main key, so can reduce the searched key
5196 // interval:
5197 {
5198 // determine which key range comes into question, taking selection tolerance
5199 // around pos into account:
5200 double posKeyMin, posKeyMax, dummy;
5201 pixelsToCoords(pos - QPointF(mParentPlot->selectionTolerance(),
5202 mParentPlot->selectionTolerance()),
5203 posKeyMin, dummy);
5204 pixelsToCoords(pos + QPointF(mParentPlot->selectionTolerance(),
5205 mParentPlot->selectionTolerance()),
5206 posKeyMax, dummy);
5207 if (posKeyMin > posKeyMax) qSwap(posKeyMin, posKeyMax);
5208 begin = mDataContainer->findBegin(posKeyMin, true);
5209 end = mDataContainer->findEnd(posKeyMax, true);
5210 }
5211 if (begin == end) return -1;
5212 QCPRange keyRange(mKeyAxis->range());
5213 QCPRange valueRange(mValueAxis->range());
5214 for (typename QCPDataContainer<DataType>::const_iterator it = begin;
5215 it != end; ++it) {
5216 const double mainKey = it->mainKey();
5217 const double mainValue = it->mainValue();
5218 if (keyRange.contains(mainKey) &&
5219 valueRange.contains(
5220 mainValue)) // make sure data point is inside visible range, for
5221 // speedup in cases where sort key isn't main key and
5222 // we iterate over all points
5223 {
5224 const double currentDistSqr =
5225 QCPVector2D(coordsToPixels(mainKey, mainValue) - pos).lengthSquared();
5226 if (currentDistSqr < minDistSqr) {
5227 minDistSqr = currentDistSqr;
5228 minDistIndex = int(it - mDataContainer->constBegin());
5229 }
5230 }
5231 }
5232 if (minDistIndex != mDataContainer->size())
5233 selectionResult.addDataRange(QCPDataRange(minDistIndex, minDistIndex + 1),
5234 false);
5235
5236 selectionResult.simplify();
5237 if (details) details->setValue(selectionResult);
5238 return qSqrt(minDistSqr);
5239}
5240
5251template <class DataType>
5252void QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::getDataSegments(
5253 QList<QCPDataRange> &selectedSegments,
5254 QList<QCPDataRange> &unselectedSegments) const {
5255 selectedSegments.clear();
5256 unselectedSegments.clear();
5257 if (mSelectable ==
5258 QCP::stWhole) // stWhole selection type draws the entire plottable with
5259 // selected style if mSelection isn't empty
5260 {
5261 if (selected())
5262 selectedSegments << QCPDataRange(0, dataCount());
5263 else
5264 unselectedSegments << QCPDataRange(0, dataCount());
5265 } else {
5266 QCPDataSelection sel(selection());
5267 sel.simplify();
5268 selectedSegments = sel.dataRanges();
5269 unselectedSegments = sel.inverse(QCPDataRange(0, dataCount())).dataRanges();
5270 }
5271}
5272
5283template <class DataType>
5284void QCPAbstractPlottable1D<DataType>::drawPolyline(
5285 QCPPainter *painter, const QVector<QPointF> &lineData) const {
5286 // if drawing lines in plot (instead of PDF), reduce 1px lines to cosmetic,
5287 // because at least in Qt6 drawing of "1px" width lines is much slower even
5288 // though it has same appearance apart from High-DPI. In High-DPI cases people
5289 // must set a pen width slightly larger than 1.0 to get correct DPI scaling of
5290 // width, but of course with performance penalty.
5291 if (!painter->modes().testFlag(QCPPainter::pmVectorized) &&
5292 qFuzzyCompare(painter->pen().widthF(), 1.0)) {
5293 QPen newPen = painter->pen();
5294 newPen.setWidth(0);
5295 painter->setPen(newPen);
5296 }
5297
5298 // if drawing solid line and not in PDF, use much faster line drawing instead
5299 // of polyline:
5300 if (mParentPlot->plottingHints().testFlag(QCP::phFastPolylines) &&
5301 painter->pen().style() == Qt::SolidLine &&
5302 !painter->modes().testFlag(QCPPainter::pmVectorized) &&
5303 !painter->modes().testFlag(QCPPainter::pmNoCaching)) {
5304 int i = 0;
5305 bool lastIsNan = false;
5306 const int lineDataSize = lineData.size();
5307 while (i < lineDataSize &&
5308 (qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).y()) ||
5309 qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).x()))) // make sure first point is not NaN
5310 ++i;
5311 ++i; // because drawing works in 1 point retrospect
5312 while (i < lineDataSize) {
5313 if (!qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).y()) &&
5314 !qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).x())) // NaNs create a gap in the line
5315 {
5316 if (!lastIsNan)
5317 painter->drawLine(lineData.at(i - 1), lineData.at(i));
5318 else
5319 lastIsNan = false;
5320 } else
5321 lastIsNan = true;
5322 ++i;
5323 }
5324 } else {
5325 int segmentStart = 0;
5326 int i = 0;
5327 const int lineDataSize = lineData.size();
5328 while (i < lineDataSize) {
5329 if (qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).y()) || qIsNaN(lineData.at(i).x()) ||
5330 qIsInf(
5331 lineData.at(i).y())) // NaNs create a gap in the line. Also
5332 // filter Infs which make drawPolyline block
5333 {
5334 painter->drawPolyline(
5335 lineData.constData() + segmentStart,
5336 i - segmentStart); // i, because we don't want to include the
5337 // current NaN point
5338 segmentStart = i + 1;
5339 }
5340 ++i;
5341 }
5342 // draw last segment:
5343 painter->drawPolyline(lineData.constData() + segmentStart,
5344 lineDataSize - segmentStart);
5345 }
5346}

6692class QCP_LIB_DECL QCPStatisticalBoxData {
6693 public:
6694 QCPStatisticalBoxData();
6695 QCPStatisticalBoxData(double key, double minimum, double lowerQuartile,
6696 double median, double upperQuartile, double maximum,
6697 const QVector<double> &outliers = QVector<double>());
6698
6699 inline double sortKey() const { return key; }
6700 inline static QCPStatisticalBoxData fromSortKey(double sortKey) {
6701 return QCPStatisticalBoxData(sortKey, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
6702 }
6703 inline static bool sortKeyIsMainKey() { return true; }
6704
6705 inline double mainKey() const { return key; }
6706 inline double mainValue() const { return median; }
6707
6708 inline QCPRange valueRange() const {
6709 QCPRange result(minimum, maximum);
6710 for (QVector<double>::const_iterator it = outliers.constBegin();
6711 it != outliers.constEnd(); ++it)
6712 result.expand(*it);
6713 return result;
6714 }
6715
6716 double key, minimum, lowerQuartile, median, upperQuartile, maximum;
6717 QVector<double> outliers;
6718};

8384 double coordToAngleRad(double coord) const {
8385 return mAngleRad + (coord - mRange.lower) / mRange.size() *
8386 (mRangeReversed ? -2.0 * M_PI : 2.0 * M_PI);
8387 } // mention in doc that return doesn't wrap
8388 double angleRadToCoord(double angleRad) const {
8389 return mRange.lower + (angleRad - mAngleRad) /
8390 (mRangeReversed ? -2.0 * M_PI : 2.0 * M_PI) *
8391 mRange.size();
8392 }
8393 void pixelToCoord(QPointF pixelPos, double &angleCoord,
8394 double &radiusCoord) const;
